INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Mario, why ‘in Japanese is it all right to talk, question mark,’ did he say?  Use no to soften the last verb.','マリオさんはどうして「日本語で話してもいいか」と言ったのですか。','Mario san wa, dooshite ''nihongo de hanashite mo ii ka’ to itta no desu ka.',244,29);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Because, now, since he is studying Japanese, he wants to talk in Japanese.  Use node and then kara.','今、日本語を勉強しているので日本語で話したいから。','Ima, nihongo o benkyoo shite iru node, nihongo de hanashitai kara.',245,29);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('When he did so, as for women, how did they do?   Use tara.   Use onna no hito.','そうしたら女の人はどうしましたか。','Soo shitara, onna no hito wa, doo shimashita ka.  (soo shitara = and then)',246,29);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In English, ‘at the following we will get off,’ saying, they got off the train completely.','英語で「次で降ります」と言って電車を降りてしまいました。','Eigo de, ‘tsugi de orimasu’ to itte, densha o orite shimaimashita.  (not OK to substitute tsugi ni for tsugi de in this sentence, as it sounds awkward)',247,29);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('This speech, when he spoke it to the company’s person, as for the company’s person, what did she say?    Use hanashi and hanasu in the first clause.  Use tara.','この話を会社の人に話したら会社の人は何と言いましたか。','Kono hanashi o kaisha no hito ni hanashitara, kaisha no hito wa, nan to iimashita ka.',248,29);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If he speaks in Italian, then it was good, if only, she said.  Use eba.','イタリア語で話せばよかったのにと言いました。','Itariago de hanaseba yokatta noni to iimashita.',249,29);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Hello. (speaking on the phone) I’m sorry to have kept you waiting.  Use a very polite word to mean ‘did.’','もしもし、お待たせいたしました。','Moshi moshi.  Omatase itashimashita.',1,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s Matsushita.  Very polite.  Meaning, I’m Matsushita.  				松下でございます。','。','Matsushita de gozaimasu.',2,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The other day, at the sample show I  humbly met, it is Abe Industries’ Webb.  Use senjitsu.  To say ‘I  humbly met,’ say literally ‘to honorable eyes it cost.’  Use a polite form of it is.','先日、見本市でお目にかかった阿部産業のウエッブでございます。','Senjitsu, mihonichi de, ome ni kakatta, abe sangyoo no uebbu de gozaimasu.  (senjitsu = the other day, yesterday, cf. senshuu = last week, sengetsu = last month,  cf. kono aida = konaida = the other day, recently,  sakihodo = a little while ago, earlier,  sakki = before, earlier, previous, awhile ago) (mihonichi = sample show, fair,  mihon = sample, example,  Miho has a nichi [day] when she does sample shows) (my honey is a sample of the food) (ome ni kakaru = to meet someone, humble,  kakaru is a u verb)',3,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Ah, as for that time over there, honorable care developed.  Meaning, thank you for your help.','あ、あの時はお世話になりました。','A, ano toki wa, osewa ni narimashita.  (sewa = care, osewa ni narimashita = I’m indebted to you for what you’ve done)',4,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('A little while ago, I humbly received an honorable phone call, reportedly, and.  Use soo.','先ほどお電話を頂きましたそうで。','Use de to mean and.Sakihodo, odenwa o itadakimashita soo de.',5,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since in the middle of a meeting, terrible, I humbly did a discourtesy.  Very polite.  Use de to mean since.','会議中で大変失礼いたしました。','Kaigi chuu de, taihen, shitsurei itashimashita.',6,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('No.  On an honorably busy moment, there’s no excuse.  Use tokoro.  Very polite.','いいえ、お忙しいところを申し訳ございません。','Iie.  Oisogashii tokoro o, mooshiwake gozaimasen.  (oisogashii tokoro ni, not OK)',7,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s sudden, but the other day an honorable look I humbly received, regarding our company’s products...    Use sassoku, a polite word for sudden. Use goran to mean an honorable look.  Use a plain speech form of I received.  									早速ですが先日ごらん頂いたわが社の製品について、','、','Sassoku desu ga, senjitsu, goran itadaita, wagasha no seihin ni tsuite,  (kyuu desu ga, also OK, but not polite enough here) (sassoku = immediately, at once, sudden,  sassoku desu ga = this is a bit sudden, but) (itadaita = itadakimashita,  goran ni natte itadaita, also OK) (goran o itadaita, not OK, goran is not used as an object) (wagasha = our company,  waga = one’s, my, our etc.,  our dog waga the taila,  wagaya = my house) (seihin = manufactured product,  the sailing Hindu carried products,  cf. shinamono = merchandise, article,  shoohin = goods, merchandise, prize,  show Hindus the merchandise)',8,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('a little bit more, I would like to humbly explain, I think, and.  Use te to mean and.','もう少しご説明したいと思いまして。','Moo sukoshi, go setsumei shitai to omoimashite.  (go setsumei itashitai, also OK)',9,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If the honorable cirumstances are good, I would like to do a humble visit, but.  Use a polite word for good.  Use tara.  Use ukagau.  Use no to soften the','ご都合がよろしかったらお伺いしたいのですが。','last phrase.Go tsugoo ga yoroshikattara, o ukagai shitai no desu ga.   (ukagau = to call on, to ask, to hear or be told – all humble,  go to the UK again to ask, call on, hear, or be told) (o tazune shitai, also OK, less polite, still fine)',10,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('That’s so huh.  To tell the truth, from tomorrow, to Kyushu, I am humbly scheduled to do a business trip.  Use asu.  				そうですね。実は明日から九州に出張することになっております。','。','Soo desu ne.  Jitsu wa, asu kara kyuushuu ni shutchoo suru koto ni natte orimasu.',11,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for on Thursday, since I will return and humbly come, in the case of Friday afternoon, I can humbly meet I think, but... Use nara.  Use node.  Use dekiru.','木曜日には帰ってまいりますので金曜日の午後ならお会いできると思いますが。','Mokuyoobi ni wa kaette mairimasu node, kinyoobi no gogo nara, o ai dekiru to omoimasu ga,',12,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for of  half past one, how is it probably.  Use a polite word for how. Don’t use ka.','一時半では如何でしょうか。','Ichijihan de wa, ikaga deshoo.   (ichijihan ni wa, not OK – see Lesson 6, e.g. p. 28, ‘kore de ii desu’)',13,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes, with that it’s fine.','はい、それで結構です。','Hai, sore de, kekkoo desu.',14,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Well, at  half past one,  I will visit to that way.  Use de wa.','では一時半にそちらに伺います。','De wa, ichijihan ni sochira ni ukagaimasu.',15,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Ah, please honorably wait a moment.','あ、ちょっとお待ちください。','A, chotto omachi kudasai.',16,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for  half past one, another plan was being entered humbly.  Use hoka.','一時半は他の予定が入っておりました。','Ichijihan wa, hoka no yotei ga haitte orimashita.',17,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In order not to forget, even though I did a memo in advance, I was doing carelessly.  Meaning it slipped my mind.  Use yoo ni to mean in order.  Use noni to mean even though.','忘れないようにメモをしておいたのにうっかりしていました。','Wasurenai yoo ni, memo o shite oita noni, ukkari shite imashita.  (ukkari = carelessly,  ukkari suru = to do carelessly,  in the UK, the bellhops carry the luggage carelessly) (shite orimashita, also OK) (cf. ukaru = to pass an exam)',18,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('There’s no excuse, but at 3:00 will you do and am I not able to humbly receive probably?','申し訳ありませんが、3時にして頂けませんでしょうか。','Mooshiwake arimasen ga, sanji ni shite itadakemasen deshoo ka.',19,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes, well, at 3:00, I will do a humble visit.  Use de wa.  Use a humble word for do.','はい、では3時にお伺いいたします。','Hai.  De wa, sanji ni o ukagai itashimasu.',20,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the other day, by humble phone, I did a','先日はお電話で失礼いたしました。','discourtesy.  Use a humble word for did.Senjitsu wa, odenwa de, shitsurei itashimashita.',21,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('No.  It’s nothing.  (this also means, you’re welcome)','いいえ、どういたしまして。','Iie. Doo itashimashite.',22,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I was humbly waiting.  Use both omachi and orimashita..','お待ちしておりました。','Omachi shite orimashita.',23,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say, from the division manager’s Tsuchida also, ‘regards’ I-hear-thing it is.  Meaning, he said to say hello.  Use kara.  Use yoroshiku to mean regards.  Use tono koto to mean ‘I hear thing.’  Use a polite phrase for it is.','あの、部長の土田さんからもよろしくとのことでございます。','Ano, buchoo no Tsuchida kara mo, yoroshiku to no koto de gozaimasu.  (yoroshiku = regards,  e.g. yoroshiku itte kudasai = yoroshiku otsutae kudasai = give my regards) (to no koto desu =  to no koto da = I hear that, they say that,  I hear the tonometry koto [thing] is a good way to diagnose glaucoma)',24,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for with Mr. Section Manager, since-from-old-times’s honorable acquaintance he is, reportedly, huh.  Use kara.  Use soo.','課長さんとは昔からのお知り合いだそうですね。','Kachoo san to wa, mukashi kara no oshiriai da soo desu ne.  (use san because you’re addressing kachoo)',25,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, he’s a college’s rugby club’s senior member, for sure.  Use nan to soften this.','ええ、大学のラグビー部の先輩なんですよ。','Ee, daigaku no ragubii bu no senpai nan desu yo.  (ragubii bu = rugby club,  bu = counter for books,magazines,  division,  club,  percentage 1-9,  there’s a ghost in the club)  (senpai = senior member of the same group, senior, elder, predecessor,  senior members have to buy sen [1,000] pies for the club every year) (cf. senmon = specialty)',26,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Mutually, whatever kind of busy even, as for once a year, we shall meet we are saying, but...  Use ichinen ni.  Use do.  Plain speech.   Soften the last verb.','お互いにどんなに忙しくても一年に一度は会おうと言っているんですが、','Otagai ni, donna ni isogashikute mo, ichinen ni ichido wa, aoo to itte irun desu ga,  (tagai ni = with each other, mutually, Tagalog people help each other,  otagai is commonly used, to show politeness or humility, as here)  (te mo = even if)',27,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Readily we are not able to humbly meet, for sure.  Literally, say ‘it isn’t able to cost to humble eyes.’  Don’t use dekiru.  Soften this.','中々お目にかかれないんですよ。','Nakanaka, ome ni kakarenain desu yo. (ome ni kakaru = to meet someone, humble,  literally it costs to humble eyes) (kakararenai, not OK, since kakaru is a u verb, kakar + eru)',28,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Woman company employee.  She brings honorable tea.  Use josei.  Plain speech.','女性社員。お茶を持ってくる。','Josei shain.  Ocha o motte kuru.  (josei = woman)',29,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I will do a discourtesy.  Very polite.  Go ahead.','失礼いたしました。どうぞ。','Shitsurei itashimasu.  Doozo.',30,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Excuse me.  Go ahead not honorably minding. Meaning, don’t bother about me.','すみません。どうぞおかまいなく。','Sumimasen.  Doozo okamainaku.  (doozo okamainaku = please don’t bother about me,  kamau = to mind, the camel minds,  kamainai can’t be used by itself, but it’s similar to kamawanai = to not mind, kamainaku = not minding,  kamaimasen = it doesn’t matter,  cf. komaru = to be perplexed or inconvenienced,  the doctor is perplexed by the coma that Ruth has fallen into) (this reply by Michael doesn’t mean that he won’t drink the tea he was given,  he will still drink it)',31,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('By the way, it’s the aforementioned industrial use robot’s matter, but as for at our company, not in America only... To say ‘not in America only’ convert ‘not’ to an adverb.','ところで、例の工業用ロボットの件ですがわが社ではアメリカだけでなく...','Tokoro de, rei no koogyoo yoo robotto no ken desu ga, wagasha de wa, amerika dake de naku... (koogyoo = industry,  koojoo = factory,  Conan  and Joe built a factory) (yoo = something to do, business,  yoo ga nai = be no longer useful,  yooken = business, matter or concern to be addressed,  Dwight Yoakam has business with Ken, yoo = yooji = business, errand,  ken = matter, case,   koogyoo yoo = industrial use)',32,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To Europe’s direction also, we want to advance, we are humbly thinking.  Use kangaeru.','ヨーロッパのほうにも進出したいと考えております。','Yooroppa no hoo ni mo, shinshutsu shitai to kangaete orimasu.  (shinshutsu = advance, shinshutsu suru = to advance, make one’s way,  if the Shinto priest shuts up, we can advance to the cremation,  cf.  gaishutsu suru = to go out,  yushutsu suru = to export,  yunyuu = to import,  shujutsu = surgery,  shinsatsu = medical examination,  cf. hirogeru = to expand,  cf. susumeru = to advance,  not OK to substitute susumetai for shinshutsu shitai in this sentence, since susumeru doesn’t carry the same connotation of moving forward to another place)',33,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for at this way, since we heard that the with-Europe’s-companies’ business deals are numerous...  Use ukagau to mean hear.  Use node.','こちらではヨーロッパの会社との取引が多いと伺いましたので...','Kochira de wa, yooroppa no kaisha to no torihiki ga ooi to ukagaimashita node...  (torihiki = business, dealings, transaction,  torihiki suru = do business, make a deal,  if you do business with birds, you will get a tori [bird] hickey) (ukagau = to call on, to ask, to hear or be told – all humble,  go to the UK again to ask, call on, hear, or be told)',34,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('By all means, our company’s products also, if export and we are able to humbly receive, we think, and.    Use zehi.  Use eba.  Use te to mean and.','ぜひ、わが社の製品も輸出していただければと思いまして。','Zehi, wagasha no seihin mo, yushutsu shite itadakereba, to omoimashite.  (yushutsu suru = to export,  if you shuts up, we can export) (zehi = by all means,  kitto = for sure,  zettai = definitely,  tashika ni = definitely,  kanarazu = for certain)',35,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If it’s honorable you, at least, as for 500 units per year, you sell and we are able to receive thing, isn’t it question...  Use tara.  Use nen ni.  Use no to make a noun phrase.  Use de wa nai instead of ja nai.','お宅でしたら少なくても年に500台は売っていただけるのではないか...','Otaku deshitara, sukunakutemo, nen ni gohyaku dai wa, utte itadakeru no de wa nai ka...   (otaku = polite equivalent of anata,  it can also mean the listener’s honorable home) (sukunakutemo = at least,  sukunai = few,  cf. semete = at least,  not OK to substitute semete for sukunakutemo in this sentence, since semete has a different nuance) (de wa nai ka = I’m sure, in all likelihood)',36,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I think, but how is it probably?  Use ‘to’ before ‘I think’ to show quotes.  Use no to soften the verb I think.   Use a polite word for how.','と思うのですが如何でしょうか。','To omou no desu ga, ikaga deshoo ka.',37,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To Europe fitting, model’s changes also, since we are able to do, I beg you well humbly.  Use node.  Use a very polite form of the word ‘well.’ Use itasu.','ヨーロッパに合わせて、モデルのチェンジもできますのでよろしくお願いいたします。','Yooroppa ni awasete, moderu no chenji mo dekimasu node, yoroshiku onegai itashimasu.  (awaseru = to fit to, do in accord with,  also = to join together, add up, adjust, accompany, mix together,  combine,  to introduce people to each other) (while we await serum, let''s fit, adjust, mix and introduce the patient to the doctor) (uchiawase =planning meeting, the uchi [in-group] is awake in the secretary’s room for a planning meeting) (awateru = to be in a panic) (atsumeru = to collect, bring together) (matomeru	 = to bundle together, put in order, settle, arrange, finish) (sumaseru = sumasu = to stop, transitive,  sumu = to stop, intransitive) (chenji suru = to change, alter)',38,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I understood well.','よく分かりました。','Yoku wakarimashita.',39,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Your robots, as for excellent thing, as for of recently, since even children are knowing, huh.  Use a very polite phrase to mean your.  Robots is the subject.  Use koto to mean thing.  Use kodomo.  Use kara.','お宅のロボットが優秀なことは最近では子供でも知っていますからね。','Otaku no robotto ga yuushuu na koto wa, saikin de wa, kodomo demo shitte imasu kara ne.  (saikin wa, also OK,  saikin de wa is less specific,  saikin ni wa, not OK, even though saikin seems to be a time word)  (yuushuu na = excellent, superior, outstanding,  my yukka shoes are excellent, cf. yuushoo = victory, championship,  I won a victory at the yukka show,  nyushoo suru = to win a prize) (yuushuu na koto da wa, not OK, robotto wa yuushuu na mono da, OK, but generally you use koto with yuushuu,  robotto ga yuushuu na koto is OK, but robotto wa ..., not OK) (cf. yosan = budget)',40,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I think it’s a fine honorable speech, but as for only from my thinking, at soon, a humble reply can’t be done.  Use omou.  Use watakushi.  Use kangaeru.  Don’t use wa or ga after the word reply.','結構なお話だと思いますが、私の考えだけではすぐにお返事できません。','Kekkoo na ohanashi da to omoimasu ga, watakushi no kangae dake de wa, sugu ni, ohenji dekimasen.  (kekkoo na = fine)  (sugu ni = immediately)',41,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('With the division manager also I will talk well, and while still close, I will do humble communication.  Meaning, I’ll do it soon.  Use te to mean and.  Use chikai uchi ni to mean while still close.  Use a polite word for do.','部長ともよく話しまして近いうちにご連絡いたします。','Buchoo to mo yoku hanashimashite, chikai uchi ni, go renraku itashimasu.  (hanashite, also OK, less polite)',42,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I beg you well.  Very polite.','よろしくお願いいたします。','Yoroshiku onegai itashimasu.',43,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('On an honorable busy moment, I humbly disturbed you.  Use ojama.  Use itasu.','お忙しいところをお邪魔いたしました。','Oisogashii tokoro o ojama itashimashita.  (jama = disturbance, hindrance, interference)',44,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael, why to Matsushita did he make','マイケルさんはなぜ松下さんに二回目の電話を掛けたのですか。','the 2nd phone call?  Use naze.  Use kai as a counter.  Use kakeru.  Use no to soften this.Maikerusan wa, naze matsushita san ni nikai me no denwa o kaketa no desu ka.  (nido me, also OK)  (me = counter for ordinal numbers, 1st, 2nd, etc.) (kai = counter for # of times,  niban me, not OK in this case,  ban  = counter for one’s turn, order,  also used as counter for ordinal numbers, e.g. nibanme no hikidashi)',45,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the first time, it’s because Matsushita, because in a meeting, could not talk.  Use kai as a counter.  Use de and then kara to mean because.  Use plain speech to say ‘could not talk.’','一回目は松下さんが会議中で話せなかったからです。','Ikkaime wa, matsushita san ga, 	kaigichuu de, hanasenakatta kara desu.  (matsushita san wa, not OK, since better not to use wa twice in the same clause)',46,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael, to Matsushita, what sort of thing did he request?  Use koto.','マイケルさんは松下さんにどんなことを頼みしましたか。','Maikerusan wa, matsushitasan ni donna koto o tanomimashita ka.',47,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Regarding his own company’s product, in order to explain, it’s the to meet and receive thing.  Use jibun no.  Use tame ni.  Use koto.','自分の会社の製品について説明するために会ってもらうことです。','Jibun no kaisha no seihin ni tsuite setsumei suru tame ni atte morau koto desu.  (wagasha no seihin, not OK, since wagasha means our company, and the sentence is about Michael’s company)',48,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael, when, was he scheduled to meet with Matsushita?','マイケルさんはいつ松下さんと会うことになりましたか。','Maikeru san wa, itsu, matsushitasan to au koto ni narimashita ka.  (ni au, also OK)',49,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s Friday’s 3:00.','金曜日の3時です。','Kinyoobi no sanji desu.',50,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for at Michael’s company, industrial use robots, to where do they want to export, they are thinking?  Use no to soften the last verb.','マイケルさんの会社では工業用ロボットをどこに輸出したいと思っているのですか。','Maikerusan no kaisha de wa, koogyoo yoo robotto o doko ni yushutsu shitai to omotte iru no desu ka.  (koogyoo yoo = industrial use)',51,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To Europe they want to export, they are thinking.','ヨーロッパに輸出したいと思っています。','Yooroppa ni yushutsu shitai to omotte imasu.',52,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael’s company, why, industrial use robots, by Matsushita’s company they want to export and receive, they are thinking?  Use naze.  Use no to soften the last verb.','マイケルさんの会社はなぜ工業用ロボットを松下さんの会社で輸出してもらいたいと思っているのですか。','Maikerusan no kaisha wa, naze, koogyoo yoo robotto o, matsushita san no kaisha de yushutsu shite moraitai to omotte iru no desu ka.',53,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s because, as for at Matsushita’s company, with Europe’s companies’s business deals are numerous.','松下さんの会社ではヨーロッパの会社との取引が多いからです。','Matsushita san no kaisha de wa, yoroppa no kaisha to no torihiki ga ooi kara desu.  (torihiki = businessdeal)',54,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Listening to Michael’s speech, as for Matsushita, what did he reply?','マイケルさんの話を聞いて松下さんは何と答えましたか。','Maikerusan no hanashi o kiite, matsushita san wa, nan to kotaemashita ka.',55,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('After I talk with the division manager well, I will do a reply, he replied.  Use te kara to mean after.','部長とよく話してから返事をすると答えました。','Buchoo to yoku hanashite kara,	henji o suru to kotaemashita.',56,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In the following section, use plain speech, unless otherwise indicated.  To go.  Honorific.','いらっしゃる。','Irassharu.',57,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To go.  Humble.  2 responses including the masu form.','まいる。まいります。','Mairu.  Mairimasu.',58,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To come.  Honorific.','いらっしゃる。','Irassharu.',59,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To come.  Humble.  2 responses including the masu form.','まいる。まいります。','Mairu.  Mairimasu.',60,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To be.  Honorific.','いらっしゃる。','Irassharu.',61,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To be.  Humble.  2 responses including the masu form.','おる。おります。','Oru.  Orimasu.',62,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To say or tell, or to be called.   Honorific.  2 responses, including the masu form.','おっしゃる。おっしゃいます。','Ossharu.  Osshaimasu. (OSHA’s kangaroo says and tells honorably)',63,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To say.  Humble.  4 responses, including the masu forms.  For the 2nd pair of responses, literally to say/give.','申す。申します。申し上げる。申し上げます。','Moosu.  Mooshimasu.  Mooshiageru.  Mooshiagemasu.  (the moose humbly says,  the moose humbly says and ageru [gives])',64,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To eat or drink.  Honorific.','召し上がる。','Meshiagaru.  (the mesh for the shiites agaru [raises] food and drink that they honorably eat and drink)',65,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To eat or drink.  Humble.','頂く。','Itadaku.',66,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To do.  Honorific.  2 responses, including the masu form.','なさる。なさいます。','Nasaru.  Nasaimasu.  (at NASA, we do things honorably)',67,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To do.  Humble.  2 responses, including the masu form.','いたす。いたします。','Itasu.  Itashimasu. (I humbly do Italian suits)',68,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To be doing. The honorific equivalent of te iru.','ていらっしゃる。','Te irassharu.',69,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To be doing.  The humble equivalent of te iru.','ておる。','Te oru.',70,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To be knowing.  Honorific.  Use desu.','御存知です。','Gozonji desu.',71,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To be knowing.  Humble.  Use orimasu.','存じております。','Zonjite orimasu.  (zonjiru = to humbly know,  Zondervan humbly knew that his jeans were ruined)',72,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To meet someone.  Honorific.','お会いになる。','Oai ni naru.',73,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To meet someone.  Humble.','お目にかかる。','Ome ni kakaru. (o me ni [to humble eyes] it kakaru [costs] when I humbly see or meet you) (oai suru, also OK, less polite)',74,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To think/feel.  Honorific.  Use the masu form.','思いになります。','Omoi ni narimasu.  (o omoi, not OK, but you can say o okuri ni narimasu = to honorably send)',75,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To think/feel/know.  Humble.','存じる。','Zonjiru.  (o omoi suru, not OK)',76,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To visit or ask.  Honorific.  Use the masu form.','お尋ねになります。','Otazune ni narimasu. (to honorably ask about the use of a taser at the zoo while the animals neru, i.e., sleep)',77,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To visit or ask or hear.  Humble.  2 responses including the masu form','伺う。伺います。','Ukagau.  Ukagaimasu.  (oukagai shimasu, also OK)  (when I’m in the UK again, I can humbly hear, ask or visit)',78,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To look at or see.  Honorific.','ご覧になる。','Goran ni naru. (to honorably look at the Golan Heights)',79,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To look at, see or read. Humble.','拝見する。','Haiken suru.  (I humbly see and read haiku with Ken.)',80,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Did you already honorably see that movie over there?','もうあの映画をご覧になりましたか。','Moo ano eiga o goran ni narimashita ka.',81,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('A person whom they honorably call Very Honorable Mr. Tsukino honorably came.  Use the honorific word meaning to say or tell or to be called.  Use kata to mean person.','月野様とおっしゃる方がいらっしゃいました。','Tsukino sama to ossharu kata ga, irasshaimashita.',82,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Every evening, about what time do you honorably rest?','毎晩、何時ごろ	お休みになりますか。','Maiban, nanji goro oyasumi ni narimasu ka.  (nanji goro ni, also OK)',83,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As early as possible I am humbly making an effort to rest.  Use yoo ni with itasu rather than suru.  Use the humble form of imasu.','なるべく早く休むようにいたしております。','Narubeku hayaku yasumu yoo ni itashite orimasu.',84,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If this cake is good, won’t you honorably eat one','このケーキよろしかったらもう一召し上がりませんか。','more?  Don’t use wa or ga after cake.  Use a polite word for good.  Use tara.Kono keeki yoroshikattara, moo hitotsu meshiagarimasen ka.',85,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Are you honorably knowing that company over there’s Yamamoto?','あの会社の山本さんをご存知ですか。','Ano kaisha no yamamoto san o gozonji desu ka.',86,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for section manager, to the party, he will honorably come, I wonder?  Use kashira.','課長はパーティにいらっしゃるかしら。','Kachoo wa paatii ni irassharu kashira.',87,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Section manager, to next week’s party, will you honorably come?','課長、来週のパーティーにいらっしゃいますか。','Kachoo, raishuu no paatii ni irasshaimasu ka.',88,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Ah, I will go for sure.  Plain speech.','ああ、行くよ。','Aa, iku yo.  (mairu yo, not OK, but mairimasu yo is OK)',89,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for division manager, to the party, he will','部長はパーティにいらっしゃるかな。','honorably go, I wonder?  Use kana.Buchoo wa, paatii ni irrasharu kana.',90,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('He will honorably go, I think, for sure.  Plain speech.','いらっしゃると思うよ。','Irassharu to omou yo.',91,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Division manager, to the party will you honorably come?','部長、パーティにいらっしゃいますか。','Buchoo, paatii ni irasshaimasu ka.',92,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I also will humbly go.','私もまいります。','Watashi mo mairimasu.',93,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Ah, I will go for sure.  As for you?  Plain speech.  Use a man’s word for you.','ああ、行くよ。君は。','Aa, iku yo.  Kimi wa?',94,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('So. The president also will honorably come reportedly, for sure.  Use soo twice, with two different meanings.  Plain speech.','そう。社長もいらっしゃるそうだよ。','Soo.  Shachoo mo irassharu soo da yo.',95,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Did Tanaka come?   In the next 3 responses, Tanaka is the subject.','田中さんが来ましたか。','Tanaka san ga kimashita ka.  (wa would usually be better than ga in this sentence, unless you were singling Tanaka out from a group)',96,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The passive form of a verb is commonly used','田中さんが来られましたか。','in daily speech as an honorific expression, not quite as polite as the honorific expressions already learned.  Did Tanaka come?  Use the passive form.Tanaka san ga koraremashita ka.',97,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Did Tanaka come?  Use the honorific form.','田中さんがいらっしゃいましたか。','Tanaka san ga irasshaimashita ka.',98,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to be, using the masu form.','いらっしゃいます。おります。','Irasshaimasu.  Orimasu.',99,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to call on or inquire, using the masu form.  In the 2nd response, don’t use suru.','お尋ねになります。伺います。','Otazune ni narimasu.  Ukagaimasu.  (tazunemasu also OK, but it isn’t honorific)  (oukagai shimasu, also OK)',100,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb','めしあがります。いただきます。','to drink, using the masu form.Meshiagarimasu.  Itadakimasu.',101,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to show, using the masu form.','お見せになります。お見せします。','Omise ni narimasu.  Omise shimasu.  (omise itashimasu, also OK)',102,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to come, using the masu form.','いらっしゃいます。まいります。','Irasshaimasu.  Mairimasu.',103,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to say, using the masu form.  Give 2 responses for the humble form.','おっしゃいます。申します。申し上げます。','Osshaimasu.  Mooshimasu.  Mooshiagemasu.',104,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to do, using the masu form.','なさいます。いたします。','Nasaimasu.  Itashimasu.',105,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to see, using the masu form.','ご覧になります。拝見します。','Goran ni narimasu.  Haiken shimasu.',106,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Say the honorific and humble forms of the verb to go, using the masu form.','いらっしゃいます。まいります。','Irasshaimasu.  Mairimasu.',107,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to America, when will you honorably go?','アメリカにはいついらっしゃおますか。','Amerika ni wa, itsu irasshaimasu ka.',108,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('About how long will you honorably stay in America?','どのぐらいアメリカにいらっしゃいますか。','Dono gurai amerika ni irasshaimasu ka.  (dono kurai, also OK)',109,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for this evening, where will you honorably do a meal? Use konya.','今夜はどこで食事をなさいますか。','Konya wa, doko de shokuji o nasaimasu ka.',110,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Did you see this catalogue?  Honorific.','このカタログをご覧になりましたか。','Kono katarogu o goran ni narimashita ka.',111,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Go ahead, please eat.','どうぞ、食べてください。','Doozo, tabete kudasai.',112,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes, I will humbly eat.','はい、頂きます。','Hai, itadakimasu.',113,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please bring that catalogue over there.','あのカタログを持ってきてください。','Ano katarogu o motte kite kudasai.',114,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes, I will bring humbly. Use mairimasu.','はい、持ってまいります。','Hai, motte mairimasu.  (omochi shimasu, also OK, slightly more humble)',115,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Division manager Tsuchida, Board Chairman','土田部長、クラーク会長が日本にいらっしゃったそうですね。御存知ですか。','Clark honorably came to Japan, reportedly, huh.   Use soo.  Use a plain speech form of ‘honorably came.’  Do you honorably know him?Tsuchida buchoo, kuraaku kaichoo ga nihon ni irasshatta soo desu ne.  Gozonji desu ka.  (kaichoo = chairman of the board,  Kyle is the chairman of the board)',116,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to Board Chairman Clark, as for','クラーク会長にはお子さんは何人いらっしゃいますか。','honorable children, how many honorably exist?Kuraaku kaichoo ni wa, okoson wa, nan nin irasshaimasu ka.',117,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for division manager, Board Chairman Clark, honorable sake will honorably drink a lot, did he honorably know?  Use no to make a noun phrase.','部長はクラーク会長がお酒をたくさん召し上がるのを御存知でしたか。','Buchoo wa, kuraaku kaichoo ga, osake o takusan meshiagaru no o gozonji deshita ka.',118,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for division manager, the time when he did a business trip to America, he honorably met with Board Chairman Clark, reportedly, huh.  Use soo.  Use plain speech to say ‘honorably met.’','部長はアメリカに出張したときクラーク会長とお会いになったそうですね。','Buchoo wa, amerika ni shutchoo shita toki, kuraaku kaichoo to oai ni natta soo desu ne.  (kaichoo ni oai ni, not OK, because it’s better not to use 2 ni’s close to each other)',119,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Board Chairman Clark, next week, would like to meet division manager, he was honorably saying.  Use imashita rather than irasshaimashita.','クラーク会長が来週、部長に会いたいとおっしゃっていました。','Kuraaku kaichoo ga, raishuu, buchoo ni aitai to oshatte imashita',120,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Board Chairman Clark, whether he will be able to meet division manager, he was worried honorably, for sure.  Don’t use dekiru.  Use suru rather than nasaru.','クラーク会長は部長に会えるかどうか心配していらっしゃいましたよ。','Kuraaku kaichoo wa, buchoo ni aeru kadooka, shinpai shite irasshaimashita yo.  (shinpai nasatte, also OK)',121,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To Board Chairman Clark, did you do a phone call and give to me?  Speaking to someone in your in-group.','クラーク会長に電話をしてくれましたか。','Kuraaku kaichoo ni denwa o shite kuremashita ka.',122,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes, since in the middle of going out, he didn’t honorably exist.  Use gaishutsu.  Use de to mean since.','はい、外出中でいらっしゃいませんでした。','Hai, gaishutsu chuu de, irasshaimasen deshita.  (gaishutsu suru = to go out)',123,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Again, of  later, I will do a phone call.  Use the humble word for do.','又、後で電話をいたします。','Mata, ato de, denwa o itashimasu.  (ato ni, not OK)',124,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The catalogue in question, did you humbly show it to Board Chairman Clark?','例のカタログをクラーク会長にお見せしましたか。','Rei no katarogu o kuraaku kaichoo ni omise shimashita ka.',125,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes, the moment I humbly showed it, it’s terribly good things, he honorably said.  Use tokoro to mean moment.  Use mono.','はい、お見せしましたところ大変いいものだとおっしゃいました。','Hai.  Omise shimashita tokoro, taihen ii mono da to osshaimashita.',126,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('By Board Chairman Clark, to the in-group’s company, will he come and we be able to humbly receive, it seems?  Use ni to mean from.  Use soo.','クラーク会長にうちの会社に来ていただけそうですか。','Kuraaku kaichoo ni uchi no kaisha ni kite itadake soo desu ka.  (ni is used after kaichoo because we are using itadakeru,  it means ‘from,’ i.e., we can receive from him.)',127,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yes.  He will honorably come and we will be','はい、いらしていただけそうです。','able to humbly receive, it seems.  Use irashite rather than irashatte.  Use soo.Hai.  Irashite itadake soo desu.  (irashatte doesn’t sound as good here, but OK to say irashatte imasu = irashite imasu)',128,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Michael, the president, ‘come to the president room,’ he is honorably saying for sure.  Use both yoo ni and to.  Don’t use irasshaimasu.','マイケルさん、社長が社長室に来るようにとおっしゃっていますよ。','Maikerusan, shachoo ga shachoo shitsu ni kuru yoo ni to osshatte imasu yo.',129,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for this, it’s an I-made-cookie, for sure.  Use nan to soften this.  Please honorably eat and see.','これは私が作ったクッキーなんですよ。召し上がってみてください。','Kore wa, watashi ga tsukutta kukki nan desu yo.  Meshiagatte mite kudasai.',130,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To the honorable Mr. customer.  As for the division manager, since he is humbly attending a meeting, when it finishes, he will soon humbly come.  Use deru.  Use node.  Use tara.','お客さんに。部長は会議に出ておりますので終わったらすぐまいります。','Okyakusan ni.  Buchoo wa, kaigi ni dete orimasu node, owattara, sugu mairimasu.',131,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please honorably wait at this way.','こちらでお待ちください。','Kochira de omachi kudasai.',132,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Division manager Tsuchida to the president’s secretary.','土田部長が社長の秘書に。','Tsuchida buchoo ga shachoo no hisho ni.',133,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Tomorrow’s meeting’s things, as for the president, does he honorably know?','明日の会議のことを社長は御存知ですか。','Ashita no kaigi no koto o, shachoo wa gozonji desu ka.',134,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since I would like to humbly meet the president, tomorrow, to that way I would like to humbly visit I humbly think.  Use oai suru.  Use node.  Use zonjiru.','社長にお会いしたいので明日そちらにお伺いしたいと存じます。','Shachoo ni oai shitai node, ashita, sochira ni oukagai shitai to zonjimasu.  (shachoo ni o me ni kakaritai, also OK, very polite)  (ukagau = to humbly visit, call, ask, hear,  ukagai itashitai, also OK) (sochira o oukagai, not OK) (zonjiru = to humbly think, feel, know) (omotte orimasu, also OK, not as humble)',135,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To the honorable Mr. customer.  As for division manager, since he is humbly in the next room, please honorably go to that way.','お客さんに。部長はとなりの部屋におりますからそちらにいらしてください。','Okyakusan ni.   Buchoo wa, tonari no heya ni orimasu kara, sochira ni irashite kudasai.   (irashatte, also OK)',136,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To Kathy.  I will do humble introductions.  As for this way, it’s my grandmother.  Use boku no to mean my.','キャシーに。ご紹介します。こちらはぼくの祖母です。','Kyashii ni.  Goshookai shimasu.  Kochira wa, bokuno sobo desu.  (sobo = grandmother, grandmother is so bold, sofu = grandfather,  grandfather is so foolish)',137,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('This way, it’s father, mother, moreover older brother.  ‘This way’ is the subject.','こちらが父、母、それに兄です。','Kochira ga, chichi, haha, sore ni ani desu.',138,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Pleased to meet you.  Please be good to me.  Use a 2-word version of the 2nd sentence.','初めまして。どうぞよろしく。','Hajimemashite.  Doozo yoroshiku.',139,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Everyone.  The pleasure is ours.  Well honorably came.  Meaning welcome.','みんな。こちらこそ。よくいらっしゃいました。','Minna.  Kochira koso.  Yoku irasshaimashita.',140,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the honorable country, where is it?  Use a polite word for where.','お国はどちらですか。','Okuni wa dochira desu ka.',141,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s America.  As for grandmother, how honorably old is she?','アメリカです。おばあさんはおいくつですか。','Amerika desu.  Obaasan wa oikutsu desu ka.',142,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s 78 years.','78歳です。','Nanajuu hassai desu.',143,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Honorably healthy appearing it is, huh.  Use soo.','お元気そうですね。','Ogenki soo desu ne.  (genki is a na adjective)  (if you say ogenki soo da, it means ‘reportedly you are healthy’)',144,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It it a Miss Student, or is it something work you are doing honorably?  Use a polite word for ‘being’ but not for ‘do.’ Soften this.','学生さんですか、それとも何か仕事をしていらっしゃるんですか。','Gakusei san desu ka, soretomo nanika shigoto o shite irassharun desu ka.  (shigoto o nasatte, also OK, but too polite)',145,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('A newspaper reporter of the New York Times I am doing.','ニューヨークタイムズの新聞記者をしています。','Nyuuyooku taimusu no shinbun kisha o shite imasu.  (kisha = reporter, train with steam locomotive,  the Irish reporter kisses shamrocks)',146,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for honorable Mother, something honorable','お母さんは何かお仕事をなさっているんですか。','work are you honorably doing?  Don’t use irassharu.  Soften this.Okaasan wa, nanika oshigoto o nasatte irun desu ka.',147,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At a university, I am teaching English, for sure.  Soften this.','大学で英語を教えているんですよ。','Daigaku de eigo o oshiete irun desu yo.',148,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Kathy, now, where are you living honorably?  Soften this.','キャシーさんは今どこに住んでいらっしゃるんですか。','Kyashii san wa ima doko ni sunde irassharun desu ka.  (use ni with sumu)',149,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I am living in Roppongi.','六本木に住んでいます。','Roppongi ni sunde imasu.',150,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for with Takashi, where did you get acquainted?  Soften this.','たかしとはどこで知り合ったんですか。','Takashi to wa, doko de shiriattan desu ka.  (shiriau = to meet, get acquainted)',151,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s a Roppongi’s disco.','六本木のディスコです。','Roppongi no disuko desu.',152,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('By the way, as for honorable father, what kind of honorable work are you honorably doing?  Don’t use irassharu.  Soften this.','ところでお父さんはどんなお仕事をなさっているんですか。','Tokoro de, otoosan wa, donna oshigoto o nasatte irun desu ka.',153,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At Yamakawa Trade, I am being employed, for sure.  Soften this.','山川貿易に勤めているんですよ。','Yamakawa booeki ni tsutomete irun desu yo.',154,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Kathy, America’s where at were you honorably born?  Use ni naru. Soften this.','キャシーさんはアメリカのどこでお生まれになったんですか。','Kyashii san wa, amerika no doko de o umare ni nattan desu ka.   (o umarete irasshaimashita, not OK, since that would mean ‘were being born’) (umareru = to be born, the uma [horse] rerun shows horses being born)',155,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I was born in New York.','ニューヨークで生まれました。','Nyuuyooku de umaremashita.',156,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for honorable older brother, as for honorable work, what are you honorably doing?  Don’t use irassharu.  Soften this.','お兄さんはお仕事は何をなさっているんですか。','Onii san wa, oshigoto wa, nani o nasatte irun desu ka.',157,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Television station’s announcer I am doing for sure.  Soften this.','テレビ局のアナウンサーをしているんですよ。','Terebi kyoku no anaunsaa o shite irun desu yo.',158,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Kathy, Japanese is skillful, huh.','キャシーさんは日本語が上手ですね。','Kyashii san wa, nihongo ga joozu desu ne.',159,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At where did you honorably do  study?  Use nasaru.  Soften this.','どこで勉強なさったんですか。','Doko de benkyoo nasattan desu ka.  (benkyoo o shi ni nattan, not OK,  benkyoo saremashita, also OK)',160,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At Illinois University I studied.','イリノイ大学で勉強しました。','Irinoi daigaku de benkyoo shimashita.',161,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for older brother, for honorable work, does to foreign countries honorably go thing exist?  Soften this.','お兄さんはお仕事で外国にいらっしゃることがあるんですか。','Oniisan wa oshigoto de, gaikoku ni irassharu koto ga arun desu ka.',162,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah.  Sometimes it exists for sure.','ええ、時々ありますよ。','Ee. Tokidoki arimasu yo. (cf. tama ni = occasionally)',163,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Kathy, until when, will you honorably exist in Japan?  Soften this.','キャシーさんはいつまで日本にいらっしゃるんですか。','Kyashii san wa, itsu made, nihon niirassharun desu ka.',164,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('I will exist until next year’s March.','来年の三月までいます。','Rainen no sangatsu made imasu.',165,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for big brother, as for to America to do business trip plans, do they not exist?  Soften this.','お兄さんはアメリカへ出張する予定はないんですか。','Oniisan wa, amerika e shutchoo suru yotei wa nain desu ka.',166,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('They exist, for sure.  At next year’s April, it’s a to go plan.','ありますよ。来年の四月に行く予定です。','Arimasu yo.  Rainen no shigatsu ni iku yotei desu.',167,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At the far side, if I am able to humbly meet, it’s good huh.  Use oai dekiru.  Use to.','向こうでお会いできるといいですね。','Mukoo de oai dekiru to ii desu ne.  (o me ni kakaru to, also OK, but too polite here)',168,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To express the idea even if, even though, or no matter how, use temo or demo after i adjective stems, by combining mo with their te forms.  Use temo or demo after verb stems, depending on the verb.  Use demo after na adjectives and after nouns.','日本では土曜日でも子供たちは学校に行きます。','As for in Japan, even Saturday, as for children, they go to school.  Use kodomotachi.Nihon de wa, doyoobi demo, kodomotachi wa, gakkoo ni ikimasu.',169,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to learn a foreign language time, even if','外国語を習うときは下手でもたくさんしゃべった方がいいんですよ。','unskillful, it’s better to chatter many, for sure.  Usetakusan.  Soften this.Gaikokugo o narau toki wa, heta demo, takusan shabetta hoo ga iin desu yo.  (shaberu = to talk, chat, chatter,  the Shah chatters about his berries, oshaberi  = chatterbox,  OSHA chatters about their berries)  (cf. ossharu = to say or talk, honorific) (totemo not OK,  you count shaberu, e.g. gokai shaberu = to chatter five times)',170,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Even though work is busy, as for once a month, I go for the purpose of seeing a movie.  Use tsuki ni.  Use do.','仕事が忙しくても月に一度は映画を見にいきます。','Shigoto ga isogashikutemo, tsuki ni ichido wa, eiga o mi ni ikimasu.',171,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To that person over there, even if you address him in German, he will not understand probably.','あの人にドイツ語で話しかけても分からないでしょう。','Ano hito ni, doitsugo de hanashikaketemo, wakaranai deshoo.  (hanashikakeru = to address, to speak to,  kakeru = to hang, wear glasses, sit down, spend time or money, telephone,  to kakeru [spend] hanashi [talk] is to address someone)',172,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Supposing, even if it rains, as for the sports tournament, we will hold it.','たとえ雨が降っても運動会は行います。','Tatoe, ame ga futtemo, undookai wa, okonaimasu.  (okonau = to perform, conduct, hold,  note the similar spellings for 行きますikimasu and 行いますokonaimasu)  (OK to substitute either moshi or moshimo for tatoe,  not OK to substitute tatoeba, which means ‘for example’)',173,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('How much strong male even though, as for at the parent died time, he will cry probably.  Use ikura.  Use oya to mean parent.','いくら強い男でも親が死んだときには、泣くでしょう。','Ikura tsuyoi otoko demo, oya ga shinda toki ni wa,naku deshoo.  (otoko ga ikura tsuyokutemo, also OK) (oya = parent,  we say oyasuminasai [good nignt] to our parents)',174,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Whatever kind of cold, as for me, I don’t turn on the space heater.  Use donna ni.  Use tsutoobu.','どんなに寒くても私はストーブを点けません。','Donna ni samukutemo, watashi wa sutoobu o tsukemasen.  (ikura samukutemo, also OK)',175,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the work, at the very latest, as for at 8 p.m., it will probably finish.','仕事は遅くても午後8時には終わるでしょう。','Shigoto wa, osokutemo, gogo hachiji ni wa, owaru deshoo.',176,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to the other day’s demonstration, at the very least, 2,000 people’s people participated, it seems.  Use senjitsu.  Use tomo rather than temo.  Use yoo.','先日のデモには少なくても2000人の人が参加したようです。','Senjitsu no demo ni wa, sukunakutomo, nisen nin no hito ga sanka shita yoo desu.  (OK to omit ‘no hito ga’) (senjitsu = the other day, yesterday)  (sanka = participation, sanka suru = to take part in,  I participate in drinking Sanka)',177,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the winter’s bonus, at the very most, about 3.5 month’s portion, isn’t it question?, I think.   Use plain speech to say ‘isn’t it question.’','冬のボーナスは多くても3.5ヶ月分ぐらいじゃないかと思います。','Fuyu no boonasu wa, ookutemo, san ten go kagetsu bun gurai ja nai ka to omoimasu.  (gurai bun, not OK)',178,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The temo & demo forms, meaning ‘even though,’ and noni, meaning ‘in spite of,’ are similar, but temo & demo don’t carry the emotional overtones suggested by noni.  Also, temo & demo may be used for describing hypothetical situations, while noni is not used in that way.','マイケルさんはお茶を出しても飲まなかったんです。','As for Michael, even though I put out honorable tea, he did not drink.  Use temo.  Soften the last clause.Maikerusan wa, ocha o dashitemo, nomanakattan desu.  (dashitomo, not OK, tomo is only used with adjectives, not with verbs)',179,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael, in spite of I put out honorable tea, he did not drink.  Use noni to suggest an emotional reaction.  Soften the last phrase.','マイケルさんはお茶を出したのに飲まなかったんです。','Maikerusan wa, ocha o dashita noni, nomanakattan desu.',180,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for that dictionary, even though expensive, it would be better to buy, for sure.  Use temo.','その辞書は高くても買った方がいいですよ。','Sono jisho wa, takakutemo, katta hoo ga ii desu yo.',181,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Now, since the streets are being crowded, even if you go by taxi, you will probably not be on time.  Use plain speech for the phrase ‘not be on time.’  Don’t use noni, since the situation is hypothetical.','今、道が混んでいるからタクシーで行っても間に合わないでしょう。','Ima, michi ga konde iru kara, takushii de ittemo, maniawanai deshoo.',182,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the station, it’s close, but will you go by car?','駅は近いですが車で行きますか。','Eki wa chikai desu ga, kuruma de ikimasu ka.  (eki ga, also OK, but then use kedo instead of ga to say ‘but’)',183,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, even though close, I will go by car.','ええ、近くても車で行きます。','Ee, chikakutemo, kuruma de ikimasu.',184,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Is that so?  Well, let’s call a taxi.','そうですか。じゃ、タクシーを呼びましょう。','Soo desu ka.  Ja, takushii o yobimashoo.  (yobu = to call,  call to say that the yogurt burned)',185,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for that store over there’s pizza, since it’s cheap, it isn’t delicious probably?  Don’t use ka.','あの店のピザは安いからおいしくないでしょう。','Ano mise no piza wa, yasui kara, oishikunai deshoo?',186,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('No, even though cheap it’s delicious, for sure.','いいえ、安くてもおいしいですよ。','Iie, yasukutemo oishii desu yo.',187,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Is that so?  Well, this time, I also shall eat and see.','そうですか。じゃ、今度私も食べてみましょう。','Soo desu ka.  Ja, kondo, watashi mo tabete mimashoo.  (kondo can also mean ‘next time’)',188,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the honorable bath, a little hot it might be.  Use chotto.','お風呂はちょっと熱いかもしれません。','Ofuro wa, chotto atsui kamoshiremasen.',189,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If it’s hot, please add water, huh.  Use tara.','熱かったら水を入れてくださいね。','Atsukattara, mizu o irete kudasai ne.',190,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Even though hot, it’s OK for sure.','熱くても大丈夫ですよ。','Atsukutemo, daijoobu desu yo.',191,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Is that so?  As for foreign countries’ people, as','そうですか。外国の方は熱いお風呂は苦手だと聞いていたものですから。','for hot honorable baths, since ‘it’s a weakness’ I was hearing thing’ it is.  Use a polite word for people.  Use mono to mean thing and also to suggest a reason.Soo desu ka.  Gaikoku no kata wa, atsui ofuro wa, nigate da to kiite ita mono desu kara.  (nigate na = not good at, weakness, tough customer,  the night gate is a weak point)  (not Ok to substitute koto for mono,  mono implies ‘because’)',192,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, it will rain, it might be, for sure.','明日は雨が降るかもしれませんよ。','Ashita wa, ame ga furu kamoshiremasen yo.',193,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If it rains, how will you do?  Use tara.','雨が降ったらどうしますか。','Ame ga futtara, doo shimasu ka.',194,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('When you think about it, will you go?  Use yahari.','やはり行きますか。','Yahari, ikimasu ka.',195,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, even though it will rain, I will go.','ええ、雨が降っても行きます。','Ee, ame ga futtemo ikimasu.',196,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Is that so.  Well, so as not to catch a cold, please be careful huh.  Use yoo ni.','そうですか。じゃ、風邪を引かないように気をつけてくださいね。','Soo desu ka.  Ja, kaze o hikanai yoo ni, ki o tsukete kudasai ne.',197,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for this evening, since the return will become late, at before me please sleep.','今夜は帰りが遅くなるから先に寝てください。','Use konya.  Use saki to mean ‘before me.’Konya wa, kaeri ga osoku naru kara, saki ni nete kudasai.  (konya = this evening, tonight) (saki ni = ahead, formerly)  (saki = ahead of in time or space,  sakki = a while ago)  (saki de, not OK)',198,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('No, even though late, I will be awake and waiting for sure.','いいえ、遅くても起きて待っていますよ。','Iie, osokutemo okite matte imasu yo.',199,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('So.  Well, I will make an effort to return as early as possible.  Literally, say ‘to be able only early.’','そう、じゃ、できるだけ早く帰るようにします。','Soo.  Ja, dekiru dake hayaku kaeru yoo ni shimasu.  (OK to substitute narubeku hayaku for ‘dekiru dake hayaku’,  dekiru dake is stronger, Naru-chan beckoned me to come as soon as possible)',200,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, since it’s Sunday, surely, the roads will be crowded, for sure.  Use asu.  Use dakara.  Use dooro.','あすは日曜日だからきっと道路が込んでいますよ。','Asu wa, nichiyoobi dakara, kitto, dooro ga konde imasu yo.  (OK to substitute zettai for kitto, but tashika ni is too certain & kanarazu is too strong here)',201,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If you give up on going, how?  Use no to make a noun phrase.  Use tara.','行くのを止めたらどう。','Iku no o yametara doo?  (yamu, intransitive  = to stop, cease, fall ill,  yameru, transitive = to stop, give up, resign, quit)',202,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('No, even though being crowded, I will go.','いいえ、込んでいても行きます。','Iie, konde itemo ikimasu.',203,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In that case, early morning, it would be better to leave, for sure.  Use dekakeru.','それなら、朝早く出かけた方がいいですよ。','Sore nara, asa hayaku, dekaketa hoo ga ii desu yo.  (sono nara, not OK)',204,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The condition is bad probably?  Use guai.  Soften this.','具合が悪いんでしょう。','Guai ga waruin deshoo?',205,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, if you rest, how is it?  Use asu.  Use tara.','あすは休んだらどうですか。','Asu wa, yasundara doo desu ka.',206,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, since an important meeting exists, whatever kind of condition bad even though, I am not able to rest.  Use asu.  Use taisetsu.  Use guai.  Soften the last verb.','あすは大切な会議があるからどんなに具合が悪くても休めないんです。','Asu wa, taisetsu na kaigi ga aru kara, donna ni guai ga warukutemo, yasumenain desu.  (cf. taikutsu = boring)',207,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('You are being tired probably?  Soften this.','疲れているんでしょう。','Tsukarete irun deshoo?',208,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If you return to home, how is it?  Use tara.','うちに帰ったらどうですか。','Uchi ni kaettara doo desu ka.',209,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('From now, since an important meeting exists, how much I am being tired even though, I am not able to return, for sure.  Use ima kara.  Use daiji.  Use node.  Soften the last verb.','今から大事な会議があるのでいくら疲れていても帰れないんですよ。','Ima kara, daiji na kaigi ga aru node, ikura tsukarete itemo kaerenain desu yo.  (kaeru is a u verb, so the potential form is kaereru, not kaerareru)',210,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s irritating work, probably?  Use nan to soften this.','いやな仕事なんでしょう。','Iya na shigoto nan deshoo?',211,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If you refuse it, how is it?  Use tara.','断ったらどうですか。','Kotowattara doo desu ka. (kotowaru = decline, refuse,  this is a u verb)',212,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since another to do person doesn’t exist, how much irritating work even though I am not able to refuse, for sure.  Use hoka ni.  Soften the last verb.','他にする人はいないからいくらいやな仕事でも断れないんですよ。','Hoka ni suru hito ga inai kara, ikura iya na shigoto demo kotowarenain desu yo. (hoka no, not OK to modify a verb, but hoka no hito , for example, would be OK, modifying a noun) (kotowaru is a u verb)',213,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Money doesn’t exist probably?  Soften this.','お金がないんでしょう。','Okane ga nain deshoo?',214,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If you borrow from the honorable parents, how is it?  Use ni rather than kara.  Use tara.','ご両親に借りたらどうですか。','Go ryooshin ni karitara doo desu ka.',215,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the parents, now, since they are in the','両親は今、旅行中なのでお金を借りたくても借りられないんですよ。','middle of travel, even though I want to borrow money, I cannot borrow, for sure.Use node and therefore use a substitute for da.  Soften the last verb.Ryooshin wa, ima, ryokoochuu na node, okane o karitakutemo, karirarenain desu yo.  (okane ga, also OK) (kariru = to borrow,  karirareru = karireru = to be able to borrow,  karirenain desu, also OK)',216,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The stomach’s condition is bad probably?  Use i.  Use guai. Soften this.','胃の具合が悪いんでしょう。','I no guai ga waruin deshoo?',217,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If you stop to drink honorable sake, how is that?  Meaning, if you stop drinking sake.  Use no to make','お酒を飲むのを止めたらどうですか。','a noun phrase.  Use yameru.  Use tara.Osake o nomu no o yametara doo desu ka.',218,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since I like, how much the stomach’s condition is bad even though, readily I cannot stop, for sure.  Soften the last verb.  Use dakara.','好きだからいくらの具合が悪くても中々やめられないんですよ。','Suki dakara, ikura no guai ga warukutemo, nakanaka yamerarenain desu yo.  (yameru = to stop,  yamerareru = yamereru = to be able to stop,  yamerenain desu, also OK)',219,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, rain, it appears, for sure.  Don’t use ga after rain.  Use rashii without desu.','明日は雨らしいよ。','Ashita wa, ame rashii yo.  (ame ga rashii, or ame ga rashii desu, both not OK,  ame ga furu rashii is OK)',220,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To go, if you stop?  Use no to make a noun phrase.  Use yameru.  Use tara.  Plain speech.','行くのを止めたら。','Iku no o yametara?',221,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Nah, even though it will rain, I will go, for sure.  Plain speech.','いや、雨が降っても行くよ。','Iya, ame ga futtemo iku yo.',222,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('This dog, how did it do?  Meaning, what’s wrong?  Don’t use wa or ga.  Plain speech.  Use no to soften this.','この犬どうしたの。','Kono inu, dooshita no?',223,30);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Health doesn’t exist, huh.  Use plain speech.  Use desu.','元気がないですね。','Genki ga nai desu ne.',224,30);
