INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To students, if a for-the-purpose-of-to-make-study quiet room exists, it’s good, but.  Use gakuseitachi.  Use tame no.  Use to to mean if.  Soften the last clause.','学生達に勉強させるための静かな部屋があるといいんですが。','Gakuseitachi ni benkyoo saseru tame no shizuka na heya ga aru to iin desu ga.',70,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The children, so much that movie appear wanting to see case, if we let them go for the purpose of seeing?  Kodomotachi is the subject.  Use garu to mean appear.  Soften the first clause.  Use tara.','子供たちがそんなにその映画を見たがっているんなら見にいかせたら。','Kodomotachi ga sonna ni sono eiga o mitagatte irun nara, mi ni ikasetara?',71,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since side dishes are too numerous, as for all, very much unable to eat.  Use te to mean since.','おかずが多すぎて全部はとても食べられません。','Okazu ga oosugite, zenbu wa, totemo taberaremasen.  (okazu = side dishes, served with rice,  occasional zoos with o [honorable] kazoos serve side dishes) (cf. kazu = number)  (subete, not as good as zenbu,  minna, not OK here)',72,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Is it all right if I leave behind?','残してもいいですか。','Nokoshitemo ii desu ka.',73,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If it is left behind, since to the dog I will make eat, it doesn’t matter, for sure. Use tara.','残ったら犬に食べさせるからかまいませんよ。','Nokottara, inu ni tabesaseru kara, kamaimasen yo.  (inu o, not OK,  sounds like someone will be made to eat the dog)',74,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for me, once a day, the dog I am making do a walk.  Use ichi nichi ni.  Use kai.  Use wo rather than ni.','私は一日に一回犬を散歩させています。','Watashi wa, ichinichi ni ikkai, inu o sanpo sasete imasu.  (inu ni, also OK)',75,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In colloquial speech, aseru is sometimes shortened to asu, saseru can be shortened to sasu.','子供に薬を飲ましたんですが中々熱が下がらないんですよ。','To the child, I made drink medicine, but, readily, the fever doesn’t go down for sure.  Use the asu form of the causative verb.  Soften both verbs.Kodomo ni kusuri o nomashitan desu ga, nakanaka, netsu ga sagaranain desu yo.  (nomaseru can be shortened to nomasu)',76,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The causative form implies that the person being made to do something is inferior to you.  If the person is equal or superior, it’s better to use the forms te morau or te itadaku.','社長さんに書いていただきましょう。','To Mr. President write and let’s receive.  (meaning, let’s have the president write for us)Shachoo san ni kaite itadakimashoo.',77,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To Kuroda, write and let’s receive.','黒田さんに書いてもらいましょう。','Kuroda san ni kaite moraimashoo.',78,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To the in-group’s child, let’s have write.','うちの子供に書かせましょう。','Uchi no kodomo ni kakasemashoo.  (kakashimashoo, not OK)',79,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for at the home, to Hiroshi, a lot of things I am making him learn.  Use mono.','うちではひろしに沢山のものを習わせています。','Uchi de wa, hiroshi ni takusan no mono o narawasete imasu.  (koto would also be OK, but you can’t say takusan no koto,  OK to say iroiro na koto o narau)',80,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Violin, swimming, abacus, English conversation, arithmetic, moreover calligraphy I am making him learn.','バイオリン、水泳、英会話、算数、それに書道を習わせています','Baiorin, suiei, soroban, eikaiwa, sansuu, sore ni, shodoo o narawasete imasu.  (suiei = swimming,  suiei joo = swimming pool,  you’re going suiming ei?,  cf. suugaku = mathematics)  (soroban = abacus,  a sorrowful band plays a song honoring the end of the abacus) (eikaiwa = English conversation,  comprises kanji for ei, as in eigo, kai, as in kaigi, and wa, or hanasu,  cf. kaiwa = conversation,  we had a conversation about Kyle’s war) (sansuu = arithmetic,  we did arithmetic in San Francisco until we got sued,  cf. sansei suru = to agree)',81,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for on Sunday, by the boy baseball team, I am making him do baseball, but huh.  Use shoonen to mean boy.  Use keredo.','日曜日には少年野球チームで野球をさせていますけれどね。','Nichiyoobi ni wa, shoonen yakyuu tiimu de yakyuu o sasete imasu keredo ne.  (shoonen = boy,  combines kanji for little, shoo, and year, nen,  show me your nen [years], boy,  cf.  shoogakkoo = elementary school,  shoonen yakyuu tiimu = little league baseball team)',82,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('My.  It’s super, huh.','まあ、すごいですね。','Maa.  Sugoi desu ne.  (maa is woman’s speech)',83,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for home, I am not making her learn anything, but every day, one each, the home’s help I am making her do.','うちはなにも習わせていませんが毎日一つずつうちの手伝いをさせています。','Uchi wa, nanimo narawasete imasen ga, mainichi hitotsu zutsu, uchi no tetsudai o sasete imasu.',84,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Monday, I will make her line up tableware.  Use a shortened form of Monday.','月曜は食器を並べさせます。','Getsuyoo wa, shokki o narabesasemasu.  (shokki = tableware, i.e., dishes, cups, silverware, hashi,  the tableware is shocking, if you stick it in an electric outlet)',85,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Tuesday, I will make her wash tableware.  Use a shortened form of Tuesday.','火曜は食器を洗わせます。','Kayoo wa, shokki o arawasemasu.',86,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Wednesday, I will make her go for the purpose of honorable errands.  Use a shortened form of Wednesday.  Use otsukai.','水曜はお使いに行かせます。','Suiyoo wa, otsukai ni ikasemasu. (tsukai = errand, from tsukau) (cf. goyoo = honorable errand, cf. yooji = business, errand,  not OK to substitute either of these for otsukai, in this case)',87,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Thursday, I will make her do the dog’s walk.  Use a shortened form of Thursday.','木曜は犬の散歩をさせます。','Mokuyoo wa, inu no sanpo o sasemasu.',88,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Friday, I will make her boil rice.  Use a shortened form of  Friday.','金曜はご飯を炊かせます。','Kinyoo wa, gohan o takasemasu.  (taku = to cook, boil, also = to burn wood, also = home,  taite imasu = I’m cooking,  in the otaku [home], we cook, boil and burn)  (not OK to substitute waku for taku in this sentence,  waku is only used for boiling water)',89,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Saturday, I will make her do the garden’s cleaning.  Use a shortened form of Saturday.','土曜は庭の掃除をさせます。','Doyoo wa, niwa no sooji o sasemasu.  (niwa = garden, yard)',90,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Sunday, not making her do help, all day long, I let her play outside.  Use a shortened form of Sunday.','日曜は手伝いをさせないで一日中外で遊ばせます。','Nichiyoo wa, tetsudai o sasenai de, ichinichi juu, soto de asobasemasu.  (ichinichi juu = all day long,  cf. ichinichi ni = in a day, e.g., ichinichi ni ikkai = ichinichi ikkai = once a day)',91,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('My!   Home also, as for a little, it would be better to make him help, I wonder.  Use sukoshi.  Use tetsudau.  Use kashira.','まあ、うちも少しは手伝わせた方がいいかしら。','Maa!  Uchi mo, sukoshi wa, tetsudawaseta hoo ga ii kashira.  (maa is woman’s speech)',92,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The comic storyteller is making the customer laugh.','落語家が客を笑わせています。','Rakugoka ga kyaku o warawasete imasu.  (rakugo = comic story,  raku = comfort, pleasure, relief,  go = language, word,  cf.  nihongo,  a comic story contains raccoon tango [words],  rakugoka = comic storyteller) (kyaku ni, not as good)',93,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Honorable mother to the baby is making drink milk.  Use miruku.','お母さんが赤ちゃんにミルクを飲ませています。','Okaasan ga akachan ni miruku o nomasete imasu.',94,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Barbara is making Michael wait.','バーバラさんがマイケルさんを待たせています。','Baabarasan ga maikerusan o matasete imasu.  (maikerusan ni, not OK, but you could say baabarasan ga maikerusan ni matte moratte imasu = Michael is waiting for Barbara, and she’s receiving)',95,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The stick throwing, to the dog he is making take and come.','棒を投げて犬に取って来させています。','Boo o nagete inu ni totte kosasete imasu.  (boo = stick, pole, club, bar,  Robin Hood’s bow is made from a stick)  (torasete kite, also OK)',96,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To the child, he is making take the apple.','子供にりんごを取らせています。','Kodomo ni ringo o torasete imasu.',97,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('He is making the horse run.','馬を走らせています。','Uma o hashirasete imasu.  (uma ni, not OK)',98,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the teacher, to the children, she is making hear the story.','先生は子供達に話を聞かせています。','Sensei wa kodomotachi ni hanashi o kikasete imasu.',99,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The causative, te form, can be combined with verbs of giving and receiving, to mean ‘let one do something.’ These verbs include','くださる、上げる、やる、いただく、もらう。部長、その仕事を私にさせてください。','kudasaru, ageru, yaru, kureru, itadaku and morau.Division manager, that work, to me, let do please.Buchoo, sono shigoto o watashi ni sasete kudasai.',100,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Well, to you, do and I receive, I shall decide.  Use a man’s word for you.  Use yaru to mean do.  Plain speech.','じゃ、君にやってもらうことにしよう。','Ja, kimi ni, yatte morau koto ni shiyoo.',101,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Mother, let me eat ice cream.  Plain speech.','お母さん、アイスクリームを食べさせて。','Okaasan, aisukuriimu o tabesasete.',102,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('If you are turning into a good child, since I will let you eat and give, huh.  Use ko to mean child.  Use ni suru to express the idea of turning into something. Use tara. Use a contracted form of ‘if you are turning.’','いい子にしてたら食べさせて上げますからね。','Ii ko ni shitetara, tabesasete agemasu kara ne.  (shitetara = shite itara)  (ni suru also = to decide)',103,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for at that store over there, coffee freely they let you drink and give to our in-group, it seems, for sure.  Use rashii.  Plain speech.','あの店ではコーヒーを自由に飲ませてくれるらしいよ。','Ano mise de wa, koohii o jiyuu ni nomasete kureru rashii yo.  (jiyuu = liberty, freedom,  jiyuu ni = freely, as one likes) (OK to use ageru instead of kureru if you mean they are giving to people outside your in-group)',104,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Well, at about 3:00, again, you will let me do a humble phone call and I will receive.  Use de wa.  Speaking to someone outside your in-group.','では3時頃に又お電話をさせていただきます。','De wa, sanji goro ni, mata, odenwa o sasete itadakimasu.  (even though this sounds rude, it is actually very polite speech)',105,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The negative te form of the causative tense, nai de, plus kudasai, means please don’t make me do such and such.','あまり残業をさせないでください。','Very much, overtime don’t make me do, please.  Use amari.Amari, zangyoo o sasenai de kudasai.',106,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Is it a to-Canada business trip?  It’s good huh.','カナダへ出張ですか。いいですね。','Kanada e shutchoo desu ka.  Ii desu ne.  (kanada e no shutchoo, also OK,  kanada ni shutchoo, also OK,  kanada ni no shutchoo, not OK)',107,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Without fail, to me, let go please.','是非、私に行かせてください。','Zehi, watashi ni ikasete kudasai.',108,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In the case of you, you can do English also, and, well, to you,  to go and I receive shall I decide?  Use a man’s word for you.  Use shi to mean and.  Plain speech.','君なら英語もできるし、じゃ、君に行ってもらうことにしようか。','Kimi nara, eigo mo dekiru shi, ja, kimi ni, itte morau koto ni shiyoo ka.  (if you say ikasete morau, that implies that the speaker wants to be sent)',109,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The wife, since it’s illness, early to let me return and I would like to receive, but.  Wife is the subject.  Use node.  Speaking to a superior.  Soften the last clause.','家内が病気なので早く帰らせていただきたいんですが。','Kanai ga, byooki na node, hayaku kaerasete itadakitain desu ga.',110,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for that, it’s worry, huh.  Plain speech.','それは心配だね。','Sore wa shinpai da ne.',111,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since it doesn’t matter, early return and give.   Plain speech.  Use nasai.','かまわないから早く帰って上げなさい。','Kamawanai kara, hayaku kaette agenasai.',112,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Excuse me.  The home’s telephone breaks down, and we cannot use it.  Don’t use wa or ga.  Use te to mean and.  Soften the last verb.','すみません。うちの電話故障して使えないんです。','Sumimasen.  Uchi no denwa koshoo shite, tsukaenain desu.   (koshoo = breakdown, mechanical malfunction,  koshoo suru = to break down) (OK to substitute kowarete for koshoo shite in this sentence)',113,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yours, let me use and can I not receive probably?  Use a polite word for yours.  Use a humble word for receive.','お宅のを使わせていただけませんでしょうか。','Otaku no o tsukawasete itadakemasen deshoo ka.  (if you say tsukatte itadakemasen, you’re asking him to use his own phone for you)',114,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, go ahead without honorable hesitation.  Use the adverbial form of nai to mean without.','ええ、どうぞご遠慮なく。','Ee, doozo go enryoo naku.  (enryoo = reluctance, hesitation,  go enryoo naku = do freely, don’t hesitate)',115,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Mother, I, want to learn piano.  Don’t use wa or ga after the word ‘I.’  Plain speech.  Use no to soften this.','お母さん、私ピアノが習いたいの。','Okaasan, watashi, piano ga naraitai no.  (piano o, also OK)',116,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since it’s humble begging, let me learn?  Use dakara.  Plain speech.  Don’t use ka.','おねがいだから習わせて？','Onegai dakara, narawasete?',117,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('In the case that you want to learn so much, it can’t be helped huh.  Use a shortened form of ‘it can’t be helped.’  Use a woman’s word for emphasis.','そんなに習いたいならしょうがないわね。','Sonna ni naraitai nara, shoo ga nai wa ne.',118,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s OK to go for the purpose of learning.  Plain speech.  Use a woman’s word for emphasis.','習いに行ってもいいわ。','Narai ni itte mo ii wa.',119,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for today’s meal cost, to me let me pay please.  Use shokuji.  Use dai to mean cost.','今日の食事代は私に払わせてください。','Kyoo no shokuji dai wa, watashi ni harawasete kudasai.',120,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Part-time work’s money came in, for sure.  Soften this.','アルバイトのお金が入ったんですよ。','Arubaito no okane ga haittan desu yo.',121,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for me, with Hanako, I want to marry.  Use a man’s word for me.  Soften this.','僕は花子さんと結婚したいんです。','Boku wa, hanako san to, kekkon shitain desu.',122,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('On this Sunday, I will meet Hanako’s father, and with Hanako to let marry and to give, I plan to humbly beg.  Use kudasaru.  Use yoo ni, like to, to indicate what will be begged.','今度の日曜日に花子さんのお父さんに会って花子さんと結婚させてくださるようにお願いするつもりです。','Kondo no nichiyoobi ni, hanako san no otoosan ni atte, hanako san to kekkon sasete kudasaru yoo ni, onegai surutsumori desu.',123,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for regarding that matter, to me also, thinking exists.  Meaning, I’m thinking about it.','その件については私にも考えがあります。','Sono ken ni tsuite wa, watashi ni mo kangae ga arimasu.  (ken = matter)',124,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To me, please let say an opinion.','私に意見を言わせてください。','Watashi ni, iken o iwasete kudasai.   (iken = opinion,  opinion about Ikea''s neighbor)  (hanasete, not OK,  hanasu = to talk,  iu = to say)',125,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Go ahead.  If want-to-say thing exists, please say anything.  Use koto.  Use tara.','どうぞ。言いたいことがあったら何でも言ってください。','Doozo.  Iitai koto ga attara, nandemo itte kudasai.',126,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The superior’s irritating parts.  Use tokoro.','上司のいやなところ。','Jooshi no iya na tokoro.  (jooshi = superior in a company,  cf. joshi = girl, woman,  cf. josei = woman, female,  Josephine Shiite is a woman, and she’s my superior) (iya na = disgusting, disturbing, uncomfortable) (tokoro = place, part, spot, time, moment)',127,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me make only copies.  Use bakari.  Use toru.','コピーばかり取らせないでください。','Kopii bakari torasenai de kudasai.  (kopii o toru = to make copies,  toru = to get, take, pick up, steal, subscribe, take a photo, hire, adopt, collect)',128,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me make tea.  In the following responses, use ireru to mean make tea or coffee.','お茶を入れさせないでください。','Ocha o iresasenai de kudasai.',129,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me make refusal phone calls.  Use kakeru.','断りの電話を掛けさせないでください。','Kotowari no denwa o kakesasenai de kudasai.  (kotowaru = to refuse,  kotowari = refusal)',130,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me do overtime until late.','遅くまで残業させないでください。','Osoku made zangyoo sasenai de kudasai.',131,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t me make do room’s cleaning.','部屋の掃除をさせないでください。','Heya no sooji o sasenai de kudasai.',132,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me go for the purpose of to buy tobacco.','タバコを買いに行かせないでください。','Tabako o kai ni ikasenai de kudasai.',133,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me drink sake by force.','お酒を無理に飲ませないでください。','Osake o muri ni nomasenai de kudasai.  (muri ni = by force, muri na = impossible, unreasonable,  muri = impossibility, unreasonableness)',134,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Please don’t make me do male company employee’s help only.  Use bakari.','男の社員の手伝いばかりさせないでください。','Otoko no shain no tetsudai bakari sasenai de kudasai.',135,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The causative passive verb form implies that someone is forced to do an action which he does not wish to do and thus suffers discomfort, etc. The person who causes the action is marked by ni, and the person who suffers the action is marked by ga or wa.  To make the causative passive form, for a u verb, combine the root, i.e. the pre-ru form, with aserareru. (aspirin era rerun) This may be shortened to asareru, by removing the first ‘er.’  (morning [asa] rerun) The shortened form is commonly used with u verbs.  However, the longer form is used with u verbs that end in su, like hanasu.','書かせられる。書かされる。','The causative passive form of the verb to write is (2 responses):Kakaserareru.  Kakasareru.',136,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The causative passive form of the verb to talk is','話させられる。','Hanasaserareru.  (as mentioned in the previous question, since hanasu ends in su, there is no short form of the causative passive tense)',137,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To make the causative passive form of an ru verb, combine the root, i.e. the pre-ru form, with saserareru.  (Saskatchewan era rerun)','食べさせられる。','The causative passive form of the verb to eat isTabesaserareru.',138,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The following 3 verbs are irregular.  The causative passive form of  the verb to go is','行かされる。','Ikasareru.  (asa [morning] rerun,  I go in the morning)',139,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The causative passive form of the verb to come is','来させられる。','Kosaserareru  (Saskatchewan era rerun,  I come to Saskatchewan)',140,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The causative passive form of the verb to do is','させられる。','Saserareru  (Saskatchewan era rerun,  I do things in Saskatchewan)',141,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the students, by the Japanese language teacher, they were made to write a composition.  Use seitotachi.  Use the shorter form of the causative passive verb.','生徒達は日本語の先生に作文を書かされました。','Seitotachi wa, nihongo no sensei ni, sakubun o kakasaremashita.  (sakubun = composition,  comprised of kanji for tsukuru = saku = to make and bun = sentence, composition,  my composition was about a sack of Kool-Aid packages and some buns,  cf. sakuban = last night) (kakaseraremashita, also OK, long form)',142,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Yoko, various helps, she is being made to do.','よう子さんは色々な手伝いをさせられています。','Yoko san wa, iroiro na tetsudai o, saserarete imasu.  (Yoko san ni iroiro na tetsudai o sasete imasu, similar meaning, but a different point of view, suggesting that the speaker is making her do them )',143,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('She is made to go for the purpose of honorable errands etc., she is made to line up the tableware etc., she is doing.  Use tari.','お使いに行かされたり食器を並べさせられたりしています。','Otsukai ni ikasaretari, shokki o narabesaseraretari shite imasu.  (tsukai = errand)',144,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for honorable mother, to the child, she is making him eat vegetables.  Use the causative verb form.','お母さんは子供に野菜を食べさせています。','Okaasan wa kodomo ni yasai o tabesasete imasu.',145,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the child, by the honorable mother he is being made to eat vegetables.  Use the causative passive verb form.','子供はお母さんに野菜を食べさせられています。','Kodomo wa okaasan ni yasai o tabesaserarete imasu.',146,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('The salesman, to the honorable wife, is making her buy cosmetics.','セールスマンが奥さんに化粧品を買わせています。','Seerusuman ga okusan ni keshoohin o kawasete imasu.  (keshoohin = cosmetics) (cf.  seerusuman ni okusan ga keshoohin o kawasarete imasu = by the salesman, the honorable wife is being made to buy cosmetics)',147,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the honorable wife, by the salesman, she is being made to buy cosmetics.  Use the shortened form of the causative passive verb.','奥さんはセールスマンに化粧品を買わされています。','Okusan wa seerusuman ni keshoohin o kawasarete imasu.  (kawaserarete is the long form)',148,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the section manager, to Hanada, honorable tea he is making her make.','課長は花田さんにお茶を入れさせています。','Kachoo wa hanada san ni ocha o iresasete imasu.',149,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Hanada, by the section manager,','花田さんは課長にお茶を入れさせられています。','honorable tea she is being made to make.  Use thecausative passive tense.Hanada san wa kachoo ni ocha o iresaserarete imasu.',150,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Honorable mother, to the child, for the purpose of shopping, she is making him go.','お母さんが子供に買い物に行かせています。','Okaasan ga kodomo ni kaimono ni ikasete imasu.',151,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for the child, by the honorable mother, for the purpose of shopping, he is being made to go.  Use the causative passive tense.','子供はお母さんに買い物に行かされています。','Kodomo wa okaasan ni kaimono ni ikasarete imasu.',152,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to do only copying, it’s irritating. Use bakari.  Use the longer causative passive form of toru.  For the next 8 responses, use no to make noun phrases.','コピーばかり取らせられるのはいやです。','Kopii bakari toraserareru no wa, iya desu.',153,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to make tea, it’s irritating.','お茶を入れさせられるのはいやです。','Ocha o iresaserareru no wa, iya desu.',154,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to make refusal’s phone calls, it’s irritating.  Use kakeru.','断りの電話を掛けさせられるのはいやです','Kotowari no denwa o kakesaserareru no wa, iya desu.  (from kakeru = to make a phone call, kake + saserareru)',155,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to do overtime until late, it’s irritating.','遅くまで残業させられるのはいやです。','Osoku made zangyoo saserareru no wa, iya desu.',156,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to do the room’s cleaning, it’s irritating.','部屋の掃除をさせられるのはいやです。','Heya no sooji o saserareru no wa, iya desu.',157,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to go for the purpose of to buy tobacco, it’s irritating.','タバコを買いに行かされるのはいやです。','Tabako o kai ni ikasareru no wa, iya desu.',158,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to drink sake by force, it’s irritating. Use the longer form of the causative passive verb.','お酒を無理に飲ませられるのはいやです。','Osake o muri ni nomaserareru no wa, iya desu. (muri ni = by force,   muri na = impossible, unreasonable)',159,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for to be made to do male company employee’s help only, it’s irritating.  Use bakari.','男の社員の手伝いばかりさせられるのはいやです。','Otoko no shain no tetsudai bakari saserareru no wa, iya desu.Chapter 26 , Part 2',160,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To express the idea of doing something without doing something else, combine the negative stem, i.e. the pre-nai form,  of verb 1 with either nai de or zuni and then add verb 2.  Of these two forms, zuni is more formal.  Also, when using zuni with suru verbs, say ‘se zuni,’ not ‘shi zuni.’','財布を持たないで出かけたので何も買えなかった。','Since I left without holding my wallet, I was not able to buy anything.  Use nai de.  Use dekakeru.  Use node.  Plain speech.Saifu o motanai de dekaketa node, nani mo kaenakatta.  (motanai = mochimasen,  from motsu, or motu)  (not OK to substitute motte inai de, as this means ‘since I wasn’t holding it’,  the negative of motsu is motanai)  (kawanakatta = did not buy,  kaenakatta = could not buy)',161,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Since I left without holding my wallet, I was not able to buy anything.  Use zuni.  Use dekakeru.  Use node.  Plain speech.','財布を持たずに出かけたので何も買えなかった。','Saifu o mota zuni dekaketa node, nani mo kaenakatta.  (not OK to substitute motte ina zuni,  the negative of motsu is motanai)',162,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, since I will do a stomach’s exam, not eating anything, please come.  Use i.  Use nai de.','明日は胃の検査をしますから何も食べないで来てください。','Ashita wa, i no kensa o shimasu kara, nanimo tabenai de kite kudasai.  (kensa = examination, investigation,  Ken saved the patient by doing a careful exam)',163,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for tomorrow, since I will do a stomach’s exam, not eating anything, please come.  Use i.  Use zuni.','明日は胃の検査をしますから何も食べずに来てください。','Ashita wa, i no kensa o shimasu kara, nanimo tabe zuni kite kudasai.',164,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for in Japan, not taking off shoes, to a room you must not enter.  Use nai de.','日本では靴を脱がないで部屋に入ってはいけません。','Nihon de wa, kutsu o nuganai de, heya ni haitte wa ikemasen.  (from nuganai = to not take off, from nugu = to remove clothing,  I took off the shoes after new goo got in them)',165,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for in Japan, not taking off','日本では靴を脱がずに部屋に入ってはいけません。','shoes, to a room you must not enter.  Use zuni.Nihon de wa, kutsu o nuga zuni, heya ni haitte wa ikemasen.',166,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('To express the idea of doing, or not doing, something in a particular state, use the past tense of  verb 1 followed by mama, meaning state, followed by verb 2.','日本では靴を履いたまま部屋に入ってはいけません。','As for in Japan, you put on the shoes state, to a room you must not enter.  Use the past tense	 of ‘put on.’Nihon de wa, kutsu o haita mama, heya ni haitte wa ikemasen.',167,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Not eating breakfast, I came to school.  Use nai de.','朝ご飯を食べないで学校に来ました。','Asagohan o tabenai de gakkoo ni kimashita.',168,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Not eating breakfast, I came to school.  Use zuni.','朝ご飯を食べずに学校に来ました。','Asagohan o tabe zuni gakkoo ni kimashita.',169,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for yesterday, not going to the company, I was sleeping at the house.  Use nai de.','昨日は会社に行かないで家で寝ていました。','Kinoo wa kaisha ni ikanai de ie de nete imashita. (ie ni neru, not OK, since a house is large,  however, you may say either beddo ni neru, or beddo de neru)',170,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for yesterday, not going to the company, I was sleeping at the house.  Use zuni.','昨日は会社に行かずに家で寝ていました。','Kinoo wa kaisha ni ika zuni ie de nete imashita.',171,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for that train, not stopping at the station, it went past.  Use ni to mean at.  Use nai de.','その電車は駅に止まらないで通りすぎました。','Sono densha wa, eki ni tomaranai de toori sugimashita.',172,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for that train, not stopping at the station, it went past.  Use zuni.','その電車は駅に止まらずに通りすぎました。','Sono densha wa, eki ni tomara zuni toori sugimashita.',173,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for my father, 3 days duration, not returning to home, at the company, he was doing work.  Use nai de.','父は、三日間うちに帰らないで会社で仕事をしていました。','Chichi wa, mikka kan, uchi ni kaeranai de, kaisha de, shigoto o shite imashita.',174,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for my father, 3 days duration, not returning to home, at the company, he was doing work.  Use zuni.','父は三日間うちに帰らずに会社で仕事をしていました。','Chichi wa, mikka kan, uchi ni kaera zuni, kaisha de, shigoto o shite imashita.',175,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for this evening, at the home, not watching TV, I will write a meeting’s report.  Use konya.  Use nai de.  Use hookokusho.','今夜はうちでテレビを見ないで会議の報告書を書きます。','Konya wa, uchi de terebi o minai de, kaigi no hookokusho o kakimasu.',176,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for this evening, at the home, not watching TV, I will write a meeting’s report.  Use zuni.','今夜はうちでテレビを見ずに会議の報告書を書きます。','Konya wa, uchi de terebi o mi zuni, kaigi no hookokusho o kakimasu.',177,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael, to Kitamura not doing greeting, to the house he returned completely.  Use nai de.','マイケルさんは北村さんに挨拶をしないで家に帰ってしまいました。','Maikerusan wa, kitamura san ni, aisatsu o shinai de, ie ni kaette shimaimashita.  (ai shite iru [I love you] and greet you with satsu [paper currency])',178,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('As for Michael, to Kitamura not doing greeting, to the house he returned completely.  Use zuni.','マイケルさんは北村さんに挨拶をせずに家に帰ってしまいました。','Maikerusan wa, kitamura san ni, aisatsu o se zuni, ie ni kaette shimaimashita.  (use se zuni, not shi zuni, after suru verbs)',179,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Not asking Michael’s circumstances, on Michael’s home he paid a visit.  Use nai de.  Use tazuneru.','マイケルさんの都合を聞かないでマイケルさんのうちを尋ねました。','Maikerusan no tsugoo o kikanai de, Maikeru san no uchi o tazunemashita.  (if referring to yourself, use ukagau) (uchi ni tazunemashita, also OK,  uchi o ukagau, uchi ni ukagau, both OK)',180,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Not asking Michael’s circumstances, on Michael’s home he paid a visit.  Use zuni.  Use tazuneru.','マイケルさんの都合を聞かずにマイケルさんのうちを尋ねました。','Maikerusan no tsugoo o kika zuni, Maikeru san no uchi o tazunemashita. (uchi ni tazunemashita, also OK,  uchi o ukagau, uchi ni ukagau, both OK)',181,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At the store, not wearing and seeing this clothing, when I bought and returned, it was too small.  Use tara.  Use nai de.','店でこの服を着てみないで買って帰ったら小さすぎました。','Mise de, kono fuku o kite minai de, katte kaettara, chiisa sugimashita.',182,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('At the store, not wearing and seeing this clothing, when I bought and returned, it was too small.  Use tara.  Use zuni.','店でこの服を着てみずに買って帰ったら小さすぎました。','Mise de, kono fuku o kite mi zuni, katte kaettara, chiisa sugimashita.',183,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('You look sleepy huh.  Use soo.','眠そうですね。','Nemu soo desu ne.',184,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah.  Today, since a test exists, last night, not sleeping, I studied for sure.  Use tesuto.  Use node.  Use nai de.  Soften this.','ええ、今日テストがあるので夕べ寝ないで勉強したんですよ。','Ee.  Kyoo, tesuto ga aru node, yuube, nenai de benkyoo shitan desu yo.',185,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah.  Today, since a test exists, last night, not sleeping, I studied for sure.  Use tesuto.  Use node.  Use zuni.  Soften this.','ええ、今日テストがあるので夕べ寝ずに勉強したんですよ。','Ee.  Kyoo, tesuto ga aru node, yuube, ne zuni benkyoo shitan desu yo.',186,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('You look cold huh.  Use soo.','寒そうですね。','Samusoo desu ne.',187,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah.  Not wearing a coat, I came completely for sure.  Use kooto.  Use nai de.  Soften this.','ええ、コートを着ないで来てしまったんですよ。','Ee.  Kooto o kinai de kite shimattan desu yo.  (cf. kiranai de = not cutting)',188,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah.  Not wearing a coat, I came completely for sure.  Use kooto.  Use zuni.  Soften this.','ええ、コートを着ずに来てしまったんですよ。','Ee.  Kooto o ki zuni kite shimattan desu yo.',189,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Ah, how shall I do?  Plain speech.  Don’t use ka.','あっ、どうしよう。','A, doo shiyoo?',190,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('How did it do?  Meaning, what’s wrong?  Use no to soften this.  Don’t use ka.  Plain speech.','どうしたの。','Doo shita no?',191,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Not turning off the gas’s fire, I went out and came.  Use nai de.  Use deru.  Plain speech.  Use a woman’s word for emphasis.','ガスの火を消さない出てきたわ。','Gasu no hi o kesanai de dete kita wa.',192,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Not turning off the gas’s fire, I went out and came.  Use zuni.  Plain speech.  Use a woman’s word for emphasis.','ガスの火を消さずに出てきたわ。','Gasu no hi o kesa zuni dete kita wa.',193,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Eh!','えっ。','Ee!',194,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('That much sweating, how did it do?  Meaning, what happened?  Don’t use wo after sweat.  Soften this.','そんなに汗かいてどうしたんですか。','Sonna ni ase kaite, dooshitan desu ka.',195,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, not boarding the bus, I ran and came.  Use nai de.  Soften the last clause.','ええ、バスに乗らないで走ってきたんです。','Ee, basu ni noranai de hashitte kitan desu.',196,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, not boarding the bus, I ran and came.  Use zuni.  Soften the last clause.','ええ、バスに乗らずに走ってきたんです。','Ee, basu ni nora zuni hashitte kitan desu.',197,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('How did it do, that much wetting?  Meaning, what happened?  Soften the first clause.  Use plain speech for the last clause.','どうしたんですか。そんなに濡れて。','Dooshitan desu ka, sonna ni nurete?',198,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, by Barbara, take an umbrella, I was told, even though, not holding I came completely.  Barbara’s husband is speaking.  Use yoo ni, instead of to.  Use the passive form of I was told.  Use nai de.  Soften the last clause.','ええ、バーバラに傘を持っていくように言われたのに持たないで来てしまったんです。','Ee, baabara ni kasa o motte iku yoo ni iwareta noni, motanai de kite shimattan desu.  (motte inai de, not OK,  the negative of motsu is motanai)',199,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Yeah, by Barbara, take an umbrella, I was told, even though, not holding I came completely.  Use yoo ni, instead of to.  Use zuni.  Soften the last clause.','ええ、バーバラに傘を持っていくように言われたのに持たずに来てしまったんです。','Ee, baabara ni kasa o motte iku yoo ni iwareta noni, mota zuni kite shimattan desu.',200,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Without receiving the division manager’s signature, did you come?  Use nai de.  Soften this.','部長のサインをもらわないで来たんですか。','Buchoo no sain o morawanai de kitan desu ka.  (morainai – no such word,  moraenai = cannot receive)',201,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Without receiving the division manager’s signature, did you come?  Use zuni.  Soften this.','部長のサインをもらわずにきたんですか。','Buchoo no sain o morawa zuni kitan desu ka.',202,31);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s bad for sure.','だめですよ。','Dame desu yo.',203,31);
