INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('Section manager Kitamura, the next work to Michael  to make do is all right isn’t it question, as for he thought thing, why is it?  Kitamura is the subject.  Use yaru rather than suru, to mean do.  Soften the word good.  Use no to make a noun phrase.  Use naze.','北村課長が今度の仕事をマイケルさんにやらせてもいいんじゃないかと思ったのはなぜですか。','Kitamura kachoo ga, kondo no shigoto o maikeru san ni yarasete mo iin ja nai ka to omotta no wa, naze desu ka.  (yaraseru = to make do,  = same meaning as saseru)',288,32);
INSERT INTO JAPANESE_LESSON(english,japanese,romaji,exercise,lesson) VALUES('It’s because Michael the with Yamakawa Trade’s business deal did cleverly.  Use umai.  Use a plain speech form of yaru.','マイケルさんが山川貿易との取引をうまくやったからです。','Maikerusan ga, Yamakawa Booeki  to no torihiki o umaku yatta kara desu.  (Maikeru san wa, not OK 290, not specific enough)',289,32);
